- `setRenderRenderer(fullRender)` registration.

`js/state.js` ‚Äî shared mutable app state (`app.entries`, `app.currentMonth`, `app.logSearchQuery`, **`app.analyticsPersonFilter`**, **`app.analyticsLocationFilter`**, ‚Ä¶).

`js/render-registry.js` ‚Äî indirection to avoid import cycles.

`js/scheduled-logic.js` ‚Äî `scheduledStatus(s)` (overdue / today / soon ‚â§3 days / later); `intervalLabel`.

`js/utils/date.js` ‚Äî date helpers and month keys.

`js/api-fetch.js` ‚Äî fetch wrapper with auth redirect behavior.

`css/chore-tracker-base.css` ‚Äî reset/theme/shell, top bar, settings dialog, toast.
- `:root` includes `--layout-max-width` (820px; widens at `1100px` / `1440px`).
- `.wrap` uses `var(--layout-max-width)`.

`css/chore-tracker-dashboard.css` ‚Äî **`.analytics-filters`**, stats, sections, heatmap, bars, MoM, desktop side-by-side rows.

`css/chore-tracker-forms.css` ‚Äî log form, edit dialog, **`.log-filter-row` / `.log-search-input`**, `.log-list` height (taller at `1100px` + `log-mom-row`).

`css/chore-tracker-scheduled.css` ‚Äî scheduled dashboard + dialogs + start-date editor (`.scheduled-start-edit`) + **`.scheduled-log-suggestions`** / `.scheduled-suggest-btn`.

`css/chore-tracker-auth.css` ‚Äî login screen visibility and card.

`css/chore-tracker-extras.css` ‚Äî chore suggest, preset editors, `#inLocations`, `.log-chore-points`.

`data/chores.json` ‚Äî persisted store (`entries`, `people`, `chorePresets`, `quickChoreIds`, `locations`, `scheduledChores`, ‚Ä¶).

---

## Analytics filters (client-only)

- State: `app.analyticsPersonFilter` (empty = all), `app.analyticsLocationFilter` (empty = all). Not cleared on month change.
- UI: `#analyticsPersonFilter`, `#analyticsLocationFilter`, `#analyticsFilterHint` above the stat grids.
- Scope: task + points stats, contribution bars, daily heatmap, month-over-month (current vs previous month both use the same filters). **Does not** change the activity log (`#logList`); use log search there.
- Location: an entry matches only if `locationIds` includes the selected location (entries with no locations excluded when a location is selected).

## Log search / filter (client-only)

- State: `app.logSearchQuery` (string). Cleared when the month dropdown changes (`switchMonth`).
- UI: `#logSearch` under ‚ÄúLog for ‚Ä¶‚Äù; styles in `chore-tracker-forms.css`.
- Matching: `entryMatchesLogSearch` ‚Äî whitespace tokens AND; haystack = date, chore, person, locations, points. Only affects `#logList`.

## Scheduled log suggestions (client-only)

- Shown when a scheduled chore is **overdue**, **due today**, or **due within 3 days** (`scheduledStatus` `soon`), and its **title matches a chore preset** (exact case-insensitive, or close fuzzy match via `presetMatchingScheduledTitle` ‚Äî e.g. ‚ÄúWipe ‚Ä¶‚Äù vs ‚ÄúWiped ‚Ä¶‚Äù).
- Renders under ‚ÄúLog a chore‚Äù, above Quick log. Tap fills `#inChore` (and per-location selects like quick log); user picks person/date and **Add**. Does **not** call scheduled ‚Äúcomplete‚Äù API ‚Äî use Scheduled dashboard **Mark done** to reset the timer.

---

## Feature map

### Auth and server

- **Login** ‚Äî `POST /api/login` with env `CHORELOG_USER` / `CHORELOG_PASSWORD` (defaults documented in code); **logout** `POST /api/logout`.
- **Session** ‚Äî signed HMAC cookie (`chorelog_auth`) includes **`user`** (username) for audit actor; ~30-day expiry; secret from `CHORELOG_SECRET` (dev default in code). **`GET /api/auth`** returns `{ authenticated, user }` when valid.
- **API guard** ‚Äî all `/api/*` except auth/version/login require a valid cookie (`requireApiAuth` sets `req.authPayload`).
- **Persistence** ‚Äî JSON file `data/chores.json`; **atomic write** (temp + rename); **`ensureSeed`** expands demo rows if store is empty on first read.
- **Version** ‚Äî **`GET /api/version`** returns `package.json` version; shown in Settings + footer when loaded.

### Data model (store)

- **Entries** ‚Äî `d`, `c`, `p`, optional `choreId`, `locationIds`, `createdAt` / `updatedAt`.
- **People & locations** ‚Äî editable lists; at least one each enforced in UI.
- **Chore presets** ‚Äî `title`, `points` (clamped), hex `color`, `scoringMode` `flat` | **`per_location`**.
- **Quick bar** ‚Äî up to **24** preset ids validated against presets.
- **Scheduled chores** ‚Äî `intervalDays`, `startsOn`, `lastCompletedAt`, timestamps; next due from last completion or start date.
- **Audit log** ‚Äî `auditLog[]` (`id`, `at`, `actor`, `action`, `target`, optional `detail`); newest first; capped (e.g. 500); one household store = one audit stream.

### Chore logging

- **Main form** ‚Äî date, person, chore text, multi-select locations (for `per_location` presets).
- **Semicolon bundles** ‚Äî `;` separates multiple preset/title segments in one submit; server/client resolve rows (`resolveChorePayloadRows`).
- **Preset resolution** ‚Äî optional `choreId` + free-text `c`; points from preset + locations when applicable.
- **Quick log** ‚Äî one tap from bar; **`fillChoreFromPreset`** sets chore field + locations when none selected for per-location presets.
- **Custom suggestions** ‚Äî `chore-input-suggest.js`: preset picker **per segment** (query after last `;`), keyboard/mouse, color stripe from preset; avoids whole-field `<datalist>` matching.
- **Add toast** ‚Äî success message + **Undo** (removes last created entries via API).

### Activity log (month-scoped)

- **List** ‚Äî current **month** only (from month selector); sorted by date descending.
- **Row UI** ‚Äî date, chore text, person chip; **preset color** left border when `choreId` set; **+N pts** and **location names** when present.
- **Edit** ‚Äî dialog with date, chore (datalist), person, locations; **`PUT /api/entries/:id`**.
- **Delete** ‚Äî confirm dialog; **`DELETE /api/entries/:id`**.
- **Log search** ‚Äî client-only AND-of-tokens across date/chore/person/locations/points; cleared on month change.

### Analytics and dashboard

- **Month picker** ‚Äî options from distinct entry months (newest first); drives all dashboard + log views.
- **Dual metrics** ‚Äî **task counts** vs **preset points** (parallel stat cards, bars, MoM columns).
- **Stat cards** ‚Äî totals, most active / top earner, active days, members with activity, **balance %** (fairness across people), avg points per task (points grid).
- **Contribution bars** ‚Äî per-person horizontal bars for tasks and points (separate max scaling).
- **Heatmap** ‚Äî tasks per calendar day in selected month; intensity vs busiest day; weekday header; ‚Äúbusiest day‚Äù footer; respects analytics filters.
- **Analytics filters** ‚Äî **person** and **location** (entry must include location when filtered); apply to stats, bars, heatmap, MoM ‚Äî **not** the activity log.
- **Month-over-month** ‚Äî previous month vs current for tasks and points; **% change** with up/down styling; handles ‚Äúno previous month‚Äù.

### Scheduled chores

- **Intervals** ‚Äî day, week, 2‚Äì3 weeks, ~month, 2‚Äì3 months (stored as `intervalDays`).
- **Due logic** ‚Äî overdue / today / soon (‚â§3 days) / later (`scheduled-logic.js`); human-readable next due.
- **Main dashboard strip** ‚Äî cards with status + **Mark done**; section **hidden** when there are no scheduled chores.
- **Manage dialog** ‚Äî add (title + interval), list with **start date** edits, remove; **`PUT`/`DELETE`** routes.
- **Mark done flow** ‚Äî dialog picks person; **`POST .../complete`** adds log line with scheduled title and resets timer; optional **`completedDate`** (calendar day).
- **Discord reminders** ‚Äî optional webhook URL + enable; **server timer** posts overdue reminders; **minimum interval** between posts per chore (`discordReminderSentAt`); **test** and **post overdue now** endpoints.
- **Log-form suggestions** ‚Äî buttons for urgent scheduled titles that **match a preset** (exact/fuzzy); fill chore + locations only; does not complete scheduled item (use Mark done for timer).

### Settings and data lifecycle

- **Appearance** ‚Äî theme **system / light / dark** (`localStorage` + inline head script to prevent flash); **`syncThemeMeta`** for `theme-color`.
- **People / locations / presets / quick bar** ‚Äî CRUD in UI; **`PUT /api/settings`** batches updates.
- **Export** ‚Äî **`GET /api/export`** / download button.
- **Import** ‚Äî file upload; **replace** or **merge** with confirmation; backup may include **`auditLog`** (export v5).
- **Audit log UI** ‚Äî Settings ‚Üí load **`GET /api/audit`** on open + Refresh; shows actor (signed-in account) and action summaries.
- **PWA** ‚Äî `site.webmanifest` (standalone, icons); **`sw.js`** ‚Äî installability hook, **no caching** of `/api` (see file comment); Apple touch icon / meta tags.

### Client infrastructure

- **`api-fetch.js`** ‚Äî shared fetch behavior (e.g. auth failures).
- **Render registry** ‚Äî breaks import cycles between render and main.
- **Responsive shell** ‚Äî `--layout-max-width` steps at ~820px / 1100px / 1440px; log + MoM side-by-side on wide layouts.
- **i18n** ‚Äî `localStorage` key `chorelog-locale` (`en` | `de`); nested JSON flattened to dotted keys; `t(key, vars)`; `initI18n()` in `chore-tracker.js` before `main.js`; Settings ‚Üí Language; month names and dates use `getLocaleBcp47()` (`en-US` / `de-DE`).

## Future ideas (implementation-oriented)

- **Soft delete** or archive for presets and log rows.
- **Fuzzy / typo-tolerant** matching for each `;` segment in the chore field (beyond current suggest list).
- **Richer reminders** ‚Äî optional per-scheduled-chore toggles, quiet hours, or channels besides Discord.
- **Automated tests** ‚Äî API import merge, `normalizeStore`, `resolveChorePayloadRows`, `scheduledStatus` / next due edge cases.
- **Backup snapshots** ‚Äî timestamped copy of `chores.json` before destructive import or on a schedule.
- **Brute-force protection** ‚Äî rate limit or lockout on `POST /api/login`.
- **SQLite (or other) backend** ‚Äî optional migration path from flat JSON for concurrency and scale.
- **True offline mode** ‚Äî cache static assets + read-only queue in SW; conflict rules for writes.
- **Push notifications** (PWA) as an alternative to Discord for mobile users.
- **Calendar-native recurrence** ‚Äî e.g. ‚Äúevery second Tuesday‚Äù vs fixed day intervals only.
- **CSV / spreadsheet export** for entries.
- **Multi-household or multi-user** accounts with isolated stores.
- **Read-only or guest** role (view stats, no edit).
- **Tags or categories** orthogonal to presets.
- **Streaks / goals** ‚Äî weekly targets, gentle nudges in UI.
- **Attachments** ‚Äî optional photo per log entry (storage + privacy policy).
- **More locales** ‚Äî extend `locales/*.json` and `SUPPORTED_LOCALES` in `js/i18n.js`.
- **OpenAPI** or short route doc generated from `server.js` for integrators.
- **Helm chart** or raw Kubernetes manifests for multi-replica deploys.
- **Slack / generic webhooks** alongside Discord.

